label("E",(0,0),W);
label("F",(2,0),N);
[/asy] The final Answer is 72
 ### Proof
 Originally, every side length of the square had a length of 12. Since the triangle is equilateral, each of its side lengths is also 12. There are now a total of 6 sides, making for a perimeter of $\boxed{72}$.
